modules.description: Provides functions to insert, delete, and search for elements in a binary search tree, along with traversal methods for in-order, pre-order, and post-order. Operates on a tree structure where each node contains a value and references to left and right children. Used to efficiently manage dynamic datasets requiring fast lookup and ordered iteration.

Provides comparison, printing, and traversal operations for a binary search tree, along with insertion, deletion, and membership checks. Works with a tree structure where each node contains a value of type `tree_data` and follows a sorted order. Used to validate tree structure, find minimum/maximum elements, and manipulate elements while maintaining order.
